# Docker Basics: Run Nginx and Apache Containers

This guide explains how to run Nginx and Apache containers using Docker and containerd/crictl.

---

## Steps

### 1. Create a GitHub Account
- Go to [GitHub](https://github.com).
- Click "Sign up".
- Enter your personal details.
- Choose a username (preferably containing your name).
- Set a secure password.

### 2. Install Docker
#### On Ubuntu/Debian:
```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install docker.io
sudo systemctl enable --now docker
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
# Log out and log back in for group changes to take effect
